[Freddy whistles]

8
00:05:33,155 --> 00:05:36,192
Look where you're goin', dear.
Look where you're goin'!

9
00:05:36,315 --> 00:05:37,509
l'm so sorry.

10
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:41,390
Two bunches o' violets trod in the mud.
A full day's wages.

11
00:05:43,035 --> 00:05:45,344
MRS. EYNSFORD-HlLL:
Freddy, go and find a cab.

12
00:05:45,435 --> 00:05:46,550
FREDDY: Yes, Mother.

13
00:05:48,675 --> 00:05:50,472
He's your son, is he?

14
00:05:50,555 --> 00:05:52,750
lf you'd done your duty
as a mother should...

15
00:05:52,835 --> 00:05:56,623
...you wouldn't let 'im spoil a poor girl's
flow'rs and run away without payin'.

16
00:05:56,715 --> 00:05:58,546
Go about your business, my girl.

17
00:05:58,635 --> 00:06:01,308
And you wouldn't go off
without payin', either.

18
00:06:01,675 --> 00:06:04,348
Two bunches o' violets trod in the mud.

19
00:06:07,075 --> 00:06:09,714
Sir, is there any sign of it stopping?

20
00:06:09,915 --> 00:06:12,304
l'm afraid not. lt's worse than before.

21
00:06:12,555 --> 00:06:14,671
lf it's worse, it's a sign it's nearly over.

22
00:06:14,755 --> 00:06:17,428
Cheer up, Capt'n,
buy a flow'r off a poor girl.

23
00:06:17,515 --> 00:06:18,868
l'm sorry, l haven't any change.

24
00:06:18,955 --> 00:06:21,469
l can change 'alf a crown.
Take this for tuppence.

25
00:06:21,555 --> 00:06:23,944
l told you, l'm awfully sorry.
Wait a minute.

26
00:06:24,035 --> 00:06:27,107
Oh, yes. Here's three ha' pence,
if that's any use to you.

27
00:06:27,195 --> 00:06:28,514
Thank you, sir.

28
00:06:36,075 --> 00:06:38,384
You be careful.
Better give 'im a flower for it.

29
00:06:38,475 --> 00:06:40,352
There's a bloke here behind that pillar...

30
00:06:40,435 --> 00:06:43,154
...takin' down every blessed word
you're sayin'.

31
00:06:46,515 --> 00:06:49,075
l ain't done nothin' wrong
by speakin' to the gentleman.

32
00:06:49,155 --> 00:06:51,794
l've a right to sell flow'rs
if l keep off the curb.

33
00:06:51,875 --> 00:06:54,025
[Shouts] l'm a respectable girl, so help me.

34
00:06:54,115 --> 00:06:57,471
l never spoke to him except to ask him
to buy a flow'r off me.

35
00:06:57,555 --> 00:06:59,989
-What's the bloomin' noise?
-A tec's takin' her down.

36
00:07:00,075 --> 00:07:01,827
l'm makin' an honest livin'.

37
00:07:01,915 --> 00:07:04,145
MAN 1 : Who's doing all that shouting?

38
00:07:05,595 --> 00:07:08,393
Sir, don't let 'im charge me.
You dunno what it means to me.

39
00:07:08,475 --> 00:07:11,353
They'll take away me character
and drive me on the streets...

40
00:07:11,435 --> 00:07:13,027
...for speakin' to gentlemen.

41
00:07:13,115 --> 00:07:16,824
There, there. Who's hurting you,
you silly girl? What'd you take me for?

42
00:07:16,915 --> 00:07:18,667
On my Bible oath, l never spoke a word.

43
00:07:18,755 --> 00:07:20,586
Shut up! Do l look like a policeman?

44
00:07:20,675 --> 00:07:23,872
Why'd ya take down me words?
'Ow do l know you took me down right?

45
00:07:23,955 --> 00:07:26,344
You just show me
what you wrote ab'ut me.

46
00:07:33,835 --> 00:07:35,951
That ain't proper writin'. l can't read it.

47
00:07:36,035 --> 00:07:36,945
l can.

48
00:07:37,035 --> 00:07:40,232
"l say, Capt'n,
now buy a flow'r off a poor girl."

49
00:07:44,075 --> 00:07:46,464
Oh, it's cause l called him "Capt'n."

50
00:07:47,035 --> 00:07:51,108
l meant no 'arm. Sir, don't let him lay
a charge against me for a word like that.

51
00:07:51,195 --> 00:07:54,471
l'll make no charge.
Really, sir, if you are a detective...

52
00:07:54,555 --> 00:07:57,547
...you needn't protect me
against molestation from young women...

53
00:07:57,635 --> 00:07:58,511
...until l ask you.

54
00:07:58,595 --> 00:08:00,870
Anyone could tell the girl meant no harm.

55
00:08:00,955 --> 00:08:03,913
He ain't no tec. He's a gentleman.
Look at his boots.

56
00:08:03,995 --> 00:08:05,906
How are all your people down at Selsey?

57
00:08:05,995 --> 00:08:08,384
Who told you my people
come from Selsey?

58
00:08:08,475 --> 00:08:09,954
Never mind, they do.

59
00:08:10,555 --> 00:08:14,309
How do you come to be up so far east?
You were born in Lisson Grove.

60
00:08:15,235 --> 00:08:18,227
What 'arm is there
in my leavin' Lisson Grove?

61
00:08:18,595 --> 00:08:21,667
lt weren't fit for pigs to live.
l had to pay four and six a week.

62
00:08:21,755 --> 00:08:23,427
Live where you like but stop that noise!

63
00:08:23,515 --> 00:08:26,905
Come, come, he can't touch you.
You've a right to live where you please.

64
00:08:26,995 --> 00:08:28,792
l'm a good girl, l am.

65
00:08:29,315 --> 00:08:31,624
-Where do l come from?
-Hawkestone.

66
00:08:31,755 --> 00:08:34,349
Who said l didn't?
Blimey, you know everything, you do.

67
00:08:34,435 --> 00:08:37,472
You, sir, do you think
you could find me a taxi?

68
00:08:37,755 --> 00:08:39,552
Madam, it's stopped raining.

69
00:08:39,635 --> 00:08:42,024
You can get a motorbus to Hampton Court.

70
00:08:42,635 --> 00:08:43,784
lsn't that where you live?

71
00:08:43,875 --> 00:08:45,513
What impertinence!

72
00:08:45,955 --> 00:08:49,345
Tell 'im where he comes from,
if you wanta go fortune-telling.

73
00:08:51,395 --> 00:08:53,192
Cheltenham, Harrow...

74
00:08:55,155 --> 00:08:56,873
...Cambridge and...

75
00:08:58,915 --> 00:08:59,950
...lndia?

76
00:09:00,035 --> 00:09:01,184
Quite right.

77
00:09:01,515 --> 00:09:03,745
MAN 2: He ain't a tec,
he's a bloomin' busybody.

78
00:09:03,835 --> 00:09:06,554
Do you do this sort of thing
for a living at a music hall?

79
00:09:06,635 --> 00:09:08,671
l have thought of it.
Perhaps l will one day.

80
00:09:08,755 --> 00:09:11,952
He's no gentleman, he ain't,
to interfere with a poor girl!

81
00:09:12,035 --> 00:09:13,673
How do you do it, may l ask?

82
00:09:13,755 --> 00:09:18,431
Simple phonetics. The science of speech.
That's my profession. Also my hobby.

83
00:09:18,875 --> 00:09:21,833
Anyone can spot an lrishman
or a Yorkshireman by his brogue...

84
00:09:21,915 --> 00:09:23,951
...but l can place a man within six miles.

85
00:09:24,035 --> 00:09:27,744
l can place 'im within two miles in London.
Sometimes within two streets.

86
00:09:27,835 --> 00:09:30,508
Ought to be ashamed of 'imself,
unmanly coward.

87
00:09:30,595 --> 00:09:32,392
